Sharp Shares Tumble Most in Four Months After Morgan Stanley Cuts Rating

-- B y   M a r i k o   Y a s u
-- 
2011-03-02T00:30:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/sharp-shares-tumble-most-in-four-months-after-morgan-stanley-cuts-rating.html
Sharp Corp. tumbled the most in four
months in Tokyo trading after Morgan Stanley cut its rating on
the stock.  The company declined as much as 5.4 percent to 841 yen, and
changed hands at 847 yen at 9:28 a.m. Morgan Stanley cut the
rating on Sharp to ‘Equalweight’ from ‘Overweight.’  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariko Yasu in 東京 at 
